Test Task for Orb IT company
Features

- User registration with email verification
- JWT authentication with access and refresh tokens
- Role-based access control: User and Admin
- Automatic deletion of unverified users via Celery
- Async architecture with SQLAlchemy and PostgreSQL
- Fully containerized with Docker

Tech Stack

- FastAPI
- SQLAlchemy 2.0 async
- PostgreSQL
- Alembic for migrations
- Celery with Redis for background tasks
- JWT for authentication
- Passlib with bcrypt for password hashing
- Docker and docker-compose

Project Structure

auth/
    router.py — authentication endpoints: signup, login, refresh, verify

core/
    config.py — environment variables and settings
    security.py — JWT token utilities

db/
    base.py — SQLAlchemy Base class
    session.py — async database session and dependency

users/
    models.py — database models: User, RefreshToken, VerificationCode
    schemas.py — Pydantic schemas for requests and responses
    repository.py — all database queries
    services.py — business logic
    router.py — user management endpoints
    dependencies.py — auth dependencies for role checking

celery_app.py — Celery configuration
tasks.py — background task for deleting unverified users
main.py — application entry point

Architecture

The project follows a layered architecture pattern:

    router receives HTTP request
    service handles business logic
    repository executes database queries
    database stores the data

Each layer only knows about its direct neighbor. Routers do not touch SQL. Repositories do not know about HTTP.

 Running with Docker (recommended)

1. Clone the repository

    git clone https://github.com/yourusername/UserManagementOrbIT.git
    cd UserManagementOrbIT

2. Create .env file from example

    cp .env.example .env

   Fill in your values:

    DATABASE_URL=postgresql+asyncpg://postgres:password@db:5432/orbdb
    SECRET_KEY=your-secret-key-here

3. Start all services

    docker-compose up --build

This will automatically:
- Start PostgreSQL and Redis
- Run Alembic migrations
- Start FastAPI application
- Start Celery worker and beat scheduler

4. Open API documentation

    http://localhost:8000/docs



Running locally without Docker

1. Install dependencies

    pip install -r requirements.txt

2. Configure .env with local database URL

    DATABASE_URL=postgresql+asyncpg://postgres:your_password@localhost:5432/orbdb
    SECRET_KEY=your-secret-key-here
    CELERY_BROKER_URL=redis://localhost:6379/0
    CELERY_RESULT_BACKEND=redis://localhost:6379/0

3. Create database

    psql -U postgres
    CREATE DATABASE orbdb;

4. Run migrations

    alembic upgrade head

5. Start the application

    uvicorn main:app --reload

6. Start Celery worker in separate terminal

    celery -A celery_app worker --loglevel=info --pool=solo

7. Start Celery beat in separate terminal

    celery -A celery_app beat --loglevel=info

PI Endpoints

Auth:
    POST /auth/signup        Register new user
    POST /auth/login         Login and get tokens
    POST /auth/refresh       Refresh access token
    POST /auth/verify        Verify email with code

Users:
    GET  /users/me           Get current user profile
    GET  /users/             Get all users (admin only)
    GET  /users/{id}         Get user by ID (admin only)
    PATCH /users/{id}        Update user data
    DELETE /users/{id}       Delete user (admin only)
    PATCH /users/me/make-admin   Grant admin role (DEV ONLY)

Testing the API

1. Register via POST /auth/signup
2. Copy verification code from terminal output
3. Verify email via POST /auth/verify
4. Login via POST /auth/login to get tokens
5. Click Authorize in Swagger UI and paste access token
6. Use PATCH /users/me/make-admin to get admin access for testing

Unverified User Cleanup

Celery automatically deletes users who have not verified their email.

Currently set to 1 minute for testing purposes.
To switch to production mode, open tasks.py and change:

    timedelta(minutes=1)  to  timedelta(days=2)

And in the beat schedule change:

    schedule=60.0  to  schedule=3600.0

Environment Variables

DATABASE_URL              PostgreSQL connection string (required)
SECRET_KEY                JWT secret key (required)
ALGORITHM                 JWT algorithm, default HS256
ACCESS_TOKEN_EXPIRE_MINUTES   Access token lifetime, default 30
REFRESH_TOKEN_EXPIRE_DAYS     Refresh token lifetime, default 7
VERIFICATION_CODE_EXPIRE_MINUTES  Verification code lifetime, default 60
CELERY_BROKER_URL         Redis broker URL
CELERY_RESULT_BACKEND     Redis result backend
